title: PolitiFact: Are most unauthorized immigrants in the U.S. working?
text:
PolitiFact: Are most unauthorized immigrants in the U.S. working? By Tom Kertscher of the Journal Sentinel Oct. 23, 2015 9:30 a.m. (0) Comments 
Do two-thirds or more of the unauthorized immigrants in the United States hold jobs? 
U.S. Sen. Ron Johnson (R-Wis.) says 8.1 million of the estimated 11 million to 12 million people "in this country illegally are working."
